Hi,

Well the context I will give you here.



There is a special centre for disabled people and their families(Known as 
Kusht Ashram).

Their child don’t get clothes and proper education and we want to start a 
campaign on that.





Write to grab attention and sympathy towards you.

Read the Reader’s mind think properly and then write



All the best!!



Regards

Daanvir India



From: Rishabh Dixit [mailto:rishabhdixit840@gmail.com]
Sent: 21 May 2018 18:11
To: anmol.alawadhi@daanvir.org
Subject: clothes and education for disabled people



Today,we are considered as one of the most emerging countries and developed 
economies of the world.But,do we are really emerging;if we see the huge gap 
between the abled and disabled people to provide needful to their children i 
can't say that.Today,all of us try to make a better future for our children 
because we can dream of;but at the same time we can't say the same for the 
disabled people as the dream also is too costly for them.Having said that ,i 
believe we should try to do something for them;as we all know clothes and 
education are one of the foremost important things and right for a person 
after food,water and shelter.I believe that by creating awareness among the 
people and by motivating them for the sake of the bright future of our 
country and mankind we should provide some basic neccessities like clothes 
and education to the children .Because,it's children who will make our 
country proud one day.


